PORTO, PORTUGAL - Porto is one of the sandwich capitals of the world and today we’re going on an ultimate Portuguese street food sandwich tour to show you some of the best sandwiches in the city! 

Huge thank you to Taste Porto (https://tasteporto.com/) for taking me on this incredible tour - they are the best! Thank you André Apolinário and Ricardo Brochado, it was amazing to hang out with them. Check them out for incredible food tours in Porto.

Here’s everything we ate on this Porto food tour: 

Casa dos Presuntos “Xico” (https://maps.app.goo.gl/s8FzyXEkCbG9dSrD7) -  This place is famous for their Presunto - a Portuguese dry cured ham, and their Salpicão - Smoked sausage with wine and paprika, which was fantastic.

O Astro (https://maps.app.goo.gl/Wt9YkkMvTFr6Ku656) - Legendary family run restaurant known for their Bifana - a classic Portuguese pork sandwich, where the pork is thin sliced and poached in their special chili laced oil and seasoning. 

Cervejaria Gazela (https://maps.app.goo.gl/mRHkeocdLXX8xXsR9) - The Cachorrinho is sometimes referred to as the Portuguese hot dog, but it’s much different - it includes bread with butter layered in sausage, hot dog, and cheese and then griddle fried and then brushed with more butter and drizzed in piri piri oil. It’s something truly amazing! 

Casa Guedes Tradicional (https://maps.app.goo.gl/hMp8VVUD135Pavqt7) - Continuing on this Portuguese street food tour we stopped at yet another legendary sandwich spot to try their melt in your mouth Sandes de Pernil - Roasted pork sandwich. 

Casa Expresso (https://maps.app.goo.gl/tDFFKwKrhdL6AjFVA) - We then headed to Rojão for their famous braised pork sandwich! 

O Golfinho (https://maps.app.goo.gl/AfJqMWvBopt3YoJ2A) - Finally on this tour we tried the king of all Portuguese sandwiches - The Francesinha - which is a massive sandwich filled with meat, cheese, and drenched in a secret sauce. If that’s not enough, you pour fries into the gravy - it’s one of the world’s greatest sandwiches! 

Thank you again to André and Ricardo from Taste Porto (https://tasteporto.com/)!
